title: Frankfurt: 1-Hour Panorama Boat Cruise on the river Main
meeting_point: Look for the KD Ticket Office with the red, blue, and white KD logo, located on the Mainkai (close to the bridge Eisener Steg). Your boat will depart right in front of the ticket office. Proceed to board the ship and present your QR-Code ticket as you enter the ship. Getting to the landing-stage by public transport: Underground station Dom/Römer or tram stop Römer/Paulskirche, both of which are a 5-minute walk from the landing-stage. Getting to the landing-stage by car: The nearest multi-storey car park is Dom/Römer in Domstraße 1. On the car park routing system follow D = Dom. From there approx. 5 min. walk to the KD landing-stage.

title: Frankfurt Airport: Fraport Visitor Center Entry Ticket
meeting_point: By airplane: The Fraport Visitor Center is located in Terminal 1, Departure Hall C, next to Gate C1, just a few steps from the gates. By car / parking facilities: The public parking garage of Frankfurt Airport is available to guests of the Visitor Center with more than 10,000 parking spaces. Drive into the P2 or P3 parking garage. From the parking garages, there is direct access to the terminal area where the Fraport Visitor Center is located. By cab / with your driver: Drive in the direction of Terminal 1, Departure C. Follow the signs to Gate C1. By public transport: From the regional train station, you can get directly to the Airport City Mall. Regional and long-distance buses stop in front of Terminal 1. Follow the signs to Terminal 1, Departure C, Gate 1.
